Convert the following extracted Purchase Order data into valid JSON conforming to the provided schema.

CRITICAL REQUIREMENTS:
- PO Number is mandatory and must be unique
- Vendor information must be complete (name required)
- At least one line item is required
- All monetary values must be positive numbers
- Line item totals should equal quantity × unit cost
- Dates should be in ISO 8601 format (YYYY-MM-DD)
- If dates are not available, omit the date fields rather than using placeholder values
- document_type must always be "purchase_order".
- If line items are grouped or subcategorized (e.g., “Electrical”, “Plumbing”), use -- to represent hierarchy in the "item_name" field, such as "Electrical -- Conduit" or "Plumbing -- Valve".
- Use consistent key casing as in the schema.

